1. Grant. Acilox grants the licensee a non-exclusive, non-transferable
   right to use the Software on the licensee's devices for the purpose
   of keeping personal cognitive-behavioural therapy thought records
   and panic-capture notes.

2. Free vs Pro tier. The free tier is available without a license key
   and includes the full thought-record form, panic capture, weekly
   digest preview, and the most recent 30 entries. The Pro tier
   (uncapped history, expanded weekly digest, encrypted backups)
   requires a paid license key obtained from https://acilox.com/labs.

3. Restrictions. The licensee may not:
   - resell, sublicense, or redistribute the Software outside the
     official Acilox distribution channels;
   - reverse engineer the license-validation logic with intent to
     bypass it;
   - share or resell Pro license keys.

4. License validation. The Software may contact
   acilox-license-worker.acilox.workers.dev (or a user-configured
   self-hosted equivalent) to validate the licensee's license key
   and to receive cached entitlement tokens. No thought-record
   contents, no panic-capture contents, no file paths, and no
   telemetry are transmitted. The only payload is the license key,
   the product id "ledger", and a stable per-install random
   identifier.

5. Data ownership. All thought-record, panic-capture, and settings
   data created in the Software remains on the licensee's device.
   Acilox neither receives nor stores any of it. Encrypted backups
   produced by the Software are the licensee's responsibility to
   safeguard; loss of the passphrase makes a backup unrecoverable.

6. Not a medical device. The Software is a structured notebook. It
